credit_line: Gift of the Estate of Herman A. Elsberg
title: Portrait
medium: Technique: Jacquard woven; Plain weave (white) patterned by warp and weft floats variously bound, and continuous supplementary wefts (yellow and rust-red) variously bound on thefront, which on the back outside the picture are bound as 3&1 twill.
description: Woven portrait of Philippe de la Salle (1723-1803) after a portrait by De Boissieu (1736-1810) and woven by Louis Reybaud.
name: Portrait
